ltiple myeloma.","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02294,0.044231,0.059366,0.070753,0.073827,0.078106,0.085457,0.090629,0.095889,0.11067,0.11914,0.149],"unified_progress":[0.023214,0.046234,0.059516,0.069846,0.074526,0.081326,0.086639,0.095147,0.1007,0.10475,0.1182,0.13991]},{"section":20,"text":"It's a plasma cell disorder where the bone marrow produces abnormal plasma cells that can cause these lytic bone lesions and systemic issues like hypercalcemia, which can lead to kidney problems and other symptoms like the ones mentioned.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030194,0.044306,0.06,0.071272,0.085829,0.095851,0.10278,0.10927,0.1119,0.10357,0.093152,0.091881],"unified_progress":[0.032559,0.053127,0.069818,0.081033,0.090071,0.099757,0.10273,0.10483,0.10336,0.099693,0.08836,0.074671]},{"section":21,"text":"I should also consider other possibilities, like metastatic cancer, but the lack of a primary tumor elsewhere and the pattern of the lesions makes myeloma more likely.","dimension":5,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.024335,0.045562,0.062201,0.071659,0.07888,0.087548,0.095028,0.10437,0.11023,0.11509,0.11206,0.093051],"unified_progress":[0.026843,0.050681,0.065112,0.07524,0.085599,0.090299,0.095863,0.10444,0.10634,0.11695,0.10045,0.082186]},{"section":22,"text":"The patient's age is 90, which is a bit older, but myeloma can occur at any age, though it's more common in older adults.","dimension":0,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035174,0.063786,0.075873,0.080151,0.084531,0.089303,0.094148,0.097732,0.10058,0.10499,0.095432,0.0783],"unified_progress":[0.050461,0.075204,0.077845,0.080794,0.086287,0.090467,0.093509,0.09723,0.095584,0.097803,0.086512,0.068303]},{"section":23,"text":"So, the most likely diagnosis is multiple myeloma.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.019553,0.039765,0.049517,0.056213,0.060536,0.065748,0.072301,0.081952,0.0